Buldhana district. Daregaon, Ta. The original budget of Sindkhed Raja Tap Water Supply Scheme was released by CEO, Zilla Parishad, Buldana vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. Also, Reference No. Under Section 1, a nominal price of Rs. 2,49,83, 200 / - has been granted by the Administrator. Also, Reference No. 5 of the Department. The bid for the additional rate of Varad scheme on 15.02.2023 has since been approved. The Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Buldana has also proposed to grant revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. The letter dated 04.10.2024 has been submitted to the government. Reference No. 3 here. Under the letter dated 25.09.2024, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Buldana.

Government Decision-: Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Dr. Daregaon, Ta. The Sindkhed Raja Tap Water Supply Scheme has been sanctioned at a cost of Rs. The revised price of 2,86,77, 038 / - (Rupees Two Crore MEM Lakh Seventy Seven Thousand and Thirty Eight only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2024 / P.No.280 / Papu13 (E Office No.933470)
Conditions
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred every year for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), reduction in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) According to a CAG report in 2013, 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity of bills due to lack of these maintenance repairs. The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned will be responsible for increasing the water tariff as per requirement so that the ARTA scheme remains financially viable.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.

2. Schemes for which tenders have been floated. The additional cost of the revised cost of the scheme, which has already been approved, should be met from the approved grant of Hao State share of Jal Jeevan Mission programme.
